assets.name: assets/4AiICNAe_9I
assets.description:
This map seeks to illustrate the tension in the VR industry between Facebook’s great success in the Oculus Rift and Quest headsets which have driven the technology forward by leaps and bounds, and their business practices and data policies which belie the company’s public commitments to act responsibility with data they collect. With this in mind, I hope that this map can help potential customers better understand how Facebook’s VR headsets differ from the rest of the market and allow people to make a more informed decision before purchasing a VR headset.

The size of the bubbles on the Map are relative to the hardware, platform, and controlling company's market share. Originally I included more headset options, but the information was too cluttered and lead to some confusion, so featured here are only the most popular options.

Sources-
"Data Policy". Facebook, 2020, https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy. Accessed 22 Sept 2020.

"Oculus Privacy Policy". Oculus.Com, 2020, https://www.oculus.com/legal/privacy-policy-for-oculus-account-users/. Accessed 22 Sept 2020.

"Steam Hardware & Software Survey". Store.Steampowered.Com, 2020, https://store.steampowered.com/hwsurvey/Steam-Hardware-Software-Survey-Welcome-to-Steam. Accessed 22 Sept 2020.

Garrison, Hugo. "Relativ | Relativty". Relativty, 2019, https://www.relativty.net/relativ/. Accessed 21 Sept 2020.

Patterson, Dan. "Facebook Data Privacy Scandal: A Cheat Sheet". Techrepublic.Com, 2020, https://www.techrepublic.com/article/facebook-data-privacy-scandal-a-cheat-sheet/. Accessed 23 Sept 2020.

Superdata 2019 Year In Review. 1st ed., Superdata, A Nielson Company, 2020, p. 19, https://www.superdataresearch.com/2019-year-in-review. Accessed 22 Sept 2020.

Taylor, Haydn. "Steam Reaches 90M Monthly Active Users". Gamesindustry.Biz, 2020, https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-10-24-steam-reaches-90m-monthly-active-users. Accessed 23 Sept 2020.

Tsai, Jason. "Press Center - Trendforce Forecasts Global VR Device Shipments At 6 Million Units In 2019, With Oculus’S Price Cut Boosting Sales | Trendforce - Market Research, Price Trend Of DRAM, NAND Flash, Leds, TFT-LCD And Green Energy, PV". Trendforce, 2020, https://www.trendforce.com/presscenter/news/20181210-10080.html. Accessed 23 Sept 2020.
